  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 425f (220c).",
    "coat the bottom of a 9x13 inch cazuela with 1 tablespoon of olive oil.",
    "in a large bowl, toss together the cauliflower, carrots, red bell pepper, onion, and garlic.",
    "spread the vegetables in an even layer in the prepared cazuela.",
    "in a small bowl, whisk together the mirin-hon, bhuna, cumin, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper.",
    "pour the mirin-hon mixture over the vegetables and toss to coat.",
    "drizzle the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil over the top.",
    "cover the cazuela with aluminum foil and bake for 25 minutes.",
    "remove the foil and continue baking for an additional 10 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender and lightly browned.",
    "remove from the oven and sprinkle with chopped parsley and feta cheese (if using)."
